        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 3:52AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 352 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Terrell County Gas Plant, or 12 miles south of
Sheffield, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Terrell County Gas Plant.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
